result.text: Dr. Antonio Agostinho Neto International Airport, crafted by China National Aero-technology International Engineering Corporation, was ready for flights on Nov. 10 in Luanda, Angola! Hosted by the Angolan Ministry of Transport, the opening ceremony had President of Angola João Lourenço unveiling and officially starting airport cargo operations. As a vital China-Angola aviation collaboration, it's the largest overseas airport project by a Chinese company. Designed for 15 million passengers and 130,000 tons of cargo annually, it aims to be a southwestern Africa hub. The Angola's Minister of Transport sees it Angola's major global gateway, driving aviation growth for around 415 million people in southern Africa.
